      "content": "That's a very detailed technical breakdown of the risks. However, if I present these points (instrumental convergence, scaling laws, etc.) to my board as \"evidence,\" it might sound like I'm validating the existential risk as a settled fact. \n\nHow would someone on the other side—the accelerationists or critics of these theories—respond to those specific technical points? Are there mainstream scientific or engineering counter-arguments to the idea that instrumental convergence or an intelligence explosion are inevitable realities?",
